bitfield.description: IP revision
Configuration of the local initiator state management mode. By definition, initiator may generate read/write transaction as long as it is out of STANDBY state.

bitenum.description: Force-standby mode: Local initiator is unconditionally placed in STANDBY state. Backup mode, for debug only.
No-standby mode: Local initiator is unconditionally placed out of STANDBY state. Backup mode, for debug only.

Smart-standby mode: Local initiator standby status depends on local conditions; that is, the module functional requirement from the initiator. IP module must not generate (initiator-related) wake-up events.

Smart-standby wakeup-capable mode: Local initiator standby status depends on local conditions; that is, the module functional requirement from the initiator. IP module may generate (master-related) wake-up events when in STANDBY state. Mode is relevant only if the appropriate IP module 'mwakeup' output is implemented.

bitfield.description: Configuration of the local target state management mode. By definition, target can handle read/write transaction as long as it is out of IDLE state.

bitenum.description: Force-idle mode: Local target IDLE state follows (acknowledges) the system idle requests unconditionally; that is, regardless of the internal requirements of the IP module. Backup mode, for debug only.
No-idle mode: Local target never enters IDLE state. Backup mode, for debug only.

Smart-idle mode: Local target IDLE state eventually follows (acknowledges) the system idle requests, depending on the internal requirements of the IP module. IP module must not generate (IRQ- or DMA-request-related) wake-up events.

Smart-idle wakeup-capable mode: Local target IDLE state eventually follows (acknowledges) the system idle requests, depending on the internal requirements of the IP module. IP module may generate (IRQ- or DMA-request-related) wake-up events when in IDLE state. Mode is relevant only if the appropriate IP module 'swakeup' output(s) is (are) implemented.
